commit.message: Generate info documentation

Make testing on emacs 29.1 work

1. ert-runner has problems with tramp (recursive load) on emacs
   29.1. Since cask deprecated the `cask exec` command anyway let's drop
   the usage of ert-runner as well. The make file try to mimic the
   ert-runner behavior to some extent to ease development work.
2. Fix new style check errors related to quotes in doc strings.

Modify supported emacs versions

Support 29.1 and drop 28.1.
Use docker for running tests locally

Fix downloading of ripgrep binary in CI

Should do exact match of package name to avoid any other downloads to
match.
Generate info documentation

It's old enough now and dependencies are dropping this as well.

fix typo: witch --> which

Add rg-finish-functions (#142)

This would allow the same functionality as
compilation-finish-functions, i.e. add hooks called when the ripgrep
process finishes.

Could for instance be used to select the *rg* buffer after a search:
(add-to-list 'rg-finish-functions (lambda (buffer _) (pop-to-buffer buffer)))
Generate info documentation
Fix sphinx documentation config

seq-set-equal-p is not available in emacs 25

Replace with own implementation based on cl-lib.

Add prioritized type aliases (#147)

Allow the user to customize a list of prioritized file type aliases
that are prioritized among ripgrep's builtin aliases.

Adjust to wgrep name changes

wgrep changed the name of wgrep-header/footer-parser. Adjust our code.

See details:
https://github.com/mhayashi1120/Emacs-wgrep/commit/3cffd82366b5713a6248d2bdb31731da8da5fe2d
Add emacs 28.2 to testing

Prefer project-root in favor of project-roots (#105)

The latter has been deprecated.

If project-root is not bound, use project-roots like before.

Be less restrictive with matching ':' in file names (#146)

This is causing troubles with line:column like patterns in files
gaining traction from ipv6 adoption. Let's just parse the filename up
until the first ':' here to improve the situation.

Fix "File: " skipping when building the elements of the imenu

We shouldn't be using `skip-chars-forward' here as this function skips
over any _character set_ passed as argument, not just a string.

Without this patch, for instance entries like:

  File: lol/foo.bar

Will be added to the candidates list as "ol/foo.bar" as ?l is in the
character set "File: ".

Instead, just skips 6 chars forward.

Revert "Disable cask package for now since it's broken"

This reverts commit a26d34ad6cbca9bae2dc72fba544af93674a0b7a.

Cask should be fixed now.

Disable cask package for now since it's broken

package-build broke cask since it has started using
package-build--get-timestamp when creating packages. Disable the
package test for now until this is fixed in cask.

Add explicit current dir ('.') on command line for darwin (#141)

Seems this is needed on Mac as well as Windows. Also added unit test
for it.

Silently fail if rename target is not found (#140)

Makes it easier to use this function in hooks etc and having a hard
error on this doesn't really makes sense.
Generate info documentation

Add imenu support

This changeset sets the buffer-local variable
`imenu-create-index-function' if `rg-group-result` is enabled,
configuring Imenu to list all the matched files and hence allowing to
quickly jump to them.

Closes #136
